text: ¬†@techTFQ¬† May I suggest a video focusing on joins? I think in particular the way you use them as a natural inner join would be something that would be really good to cover, at least based on my experience, because typically in the classes I‚Äôve been taking, they focus on joining two tables based on columns that existed in the table at the beginning. The way you tend to join, often on a created column or value, can be most beneficial, especially when you‚Äôre having trouble finding a solution.  From my experience, that type of join isn‚Äôt really being taught in classes with any depth. And I think joins in general can be a tough concept to grasp, especially when you‚Äôre coming to the field from outside of the IT arena, like I and so many others are, it might be something good to make a video about, because my guess is you would get a lot of views, and help a lot of people that way.  üôèüèª
